iftungskritik und Stiftungsaufhebung sowie um interkulturelle Imitationen im Stiftungswesen. Wie die anderen beiden Bände bietet der dritte wichtige Aufschlüsse für die Sozial- und Kulturgeschichte "mittelalterlicher" Gesellschaften und den bisher auch international erstmaligen Versuch eines interkulturellen Phänomenvergleichs mit Beiträgen zu einer transkulturellen Synthese.   aFollowing the 2014 Volume 1 devoted to “Fundamentals” and the 2015 Volume 2 on “The Social System of Foundations,” the third and final volume of the work addresses the impact of pre-modern foundations on Christian, Moslem, and Indian societies and on Jewish communities. The essays examine differences in the gender of the participants, geographical distribution, critiques of foundations, and intercultural imitations.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aCivilization, Medieval. 0aEthnic relations. 0aMiddle Ages. 4aFoundations. 4aGlobalgeschichte des Mittelalters. 4aInterkultureller Vergleich. 4aStiftungswesen. 4aTranskulturelle Beziehungen. 4aendowments. 4aintercultural comparisons. 4atranscultural entanglements. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aBorgolte, Michael , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2017z9783110547764oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831104221460 cprintz978311042580240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311042204740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110422047423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110422047.jpg  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_E